 A joint burial ceremony for four of the seven people who drowned in Kinangop on Sunday will be held on Friday in Maraigushu village. Families of the four men who perished during the incident along Maraigushu-Githabai have agreed to conduct the joint ceremony in Kanjogo primary before each family proceeds to bury their relatives. According to burial committee chairman Peter Kamau, the four who included two cousins would be laid to rest after the ceremony in their parents farms.